import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    average_price = data['price'].mean()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=['Average Price'], y=[average_price])
    plt.axhline(average_price, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Price: {average_price:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['price'])
    plt.axvline(data['price'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['price'].min():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['price'].max():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the highest and lowest price?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Price")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
